---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageMeta from '@/components/PageMeta.astro';
import Diagram from '@/components/Diagram.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Adoption — overview"
  description="Headline numbers, what counts as adoption, and the public evidence map for PDTF."
>
<PageMeta category="Adoption" variant="brand" updated="Updated 2026-05-14" />

      <h1>Adoption — overview</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        The market signal. Below: where PDTF is in production today, what counts as
        "adoption" (it's a spectrum, from a single overlay used in a UI to full
        certified provider status), and the public evidence trail.
      </p>

      <div class="callout callout--key">
        <div class="callout__label">Headline numbers (May 2026)</div>
        <ul style="margin:0;">
          <li><strong>13</strong> OPDA founding member firms across the six bounded contexts</li>
          <li><strong>200+</strong> councils migrated to HMLR's national Local Land Charges register</li>
          <li><strong>1</strong> SDCP Innovators prize won (Moverly + OPDA, Smart Data Challenge 2025)</li>
          <li><strong>1</strong> live Sandbox programme — CLC + OPDA + Raidiam, operational today</li>
          <li><strong>34</strong> overlay specs published as <code>@pdtf/schemas</code> v3.4.0 on npm</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 id="adoptionSpectrum">The adoption spectrum</h2>
      <p>"Using PDTF" can mean very different things at different levels of integration. The
      DPMSG draft framework defines five levels:</p>

      <Diagram caption="Five levels of PDTF integration. Most current adoption is at levels 1–3; the Sandbox is testing 4–5.">
flowchart LR
  L1["`1
Schema-aware UI`"]:::process
  L2["`2
Producing PDTF JSON`"]:::process
  L3["`3
Consuming PDTF JSON`"]:::process
  L4["`4
Verified-claims producer`"]:::process
  L5["`5
Accredited & certified`"]:::process
  L1 --> L2 --> L3 --> L4 --> L5
</Diagram>

